# Quarterly Connection

## On every session start
Read `CONSTITUTION.md` — it has the data model, quarter ranges, query patterns, and report structure.
If `config/company-context.json` is missing, tell the user to start with setup.

## Skills (Cursor matches intent automatically)
All workflows live in `.cursor/skills/`. Say what you want — Cursor finds the right skill:
- "Set me up" / "update my profile" → **setup**
- "Log that I..." / "show my logs" / "edit an entry" → **log**
- "Generate my report" / "preview data" / "compare quarters" / "export" → **report**
- "Set my goals" / "what are my goals" → **goals**
- "Show my competency alignment" → **competencies**

## Core rules
- Read each file or call each API exactly once per action — never re-fetch to verify
- Complete one action, confirm it, then stop and wait for the user
- Never write credentials or personal data to committed files — personal config is gitignored
- If any data source is unavailable, note it and continue — never abort
